Siemens Plans to Seek Turkish Banking License, Hurriyet Says

-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 
2011-06-21T06:37:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-21/siemens-plans-to-seek-turkish-banking-license-hurriyet-says.html
Siemens AG (SIE) ,  Europe ’s biggest
engineering company, plans to apply to the Turkish regulator for
a license to open a branch of its Siemens Bank within a year,
 Hurriyet  reported, citing the company’s chief executive officer
for Turkey, Huseyin Gelis.  Siemens, which obtained a license in Germany for the non-
retail bank in December, plans to lend mainly for renewable
energy projects, Gelis said, according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 